feed.title: Changing the Guard
feed.station: Victoria, Green Park, St Jamess Park or Hyde Park Corner
feed.description:
Changing the Guard at Buckingham Palace encompasses colourful spectacle and British pageantry. During the Changing the Guard ceremony, also known as Guard Mounting, one regiment takes over from another. The Queens Guard is made up of the St Jamess Palace and Buckingham Palace detachments. The New Guard, who during the course of the ceremony become The Queens Guard, march to Buckingham Palace from Wellington Barracks with musical accompaniment.

Check website for confirmed dates and times.
feed.shortDescription: Changing the Guard at Buckingham Palace encompasses colourful spectacle and British pageantry.

feed.title: GOOD GRIEF, CHARLIE BROWN!
feed.openingTime: Mon, Tue, Sat & Sun 10.00-18.00, Wed-Fri 11.00-20.00, except Thu 14 Feb 11.00-18.00 (last entry 1 hour prior to closing time)
feed.transport: Charing Cross(Bakerloo, Northern lines), Embankment (Circle, District lines)
feed.description: GOOD GRIEF, CHARLIE BROWN! brings together Charles M. Schulz original Peanuts cartoons with work from a wide range of acclaimed contemporary artists and designers who have been inspired by this highly influential and much-loved cartoon. Unique in its enduring appeal, this exhibition explores Peanuts renewed agency in contemporary culture and society.
feed.shortDescription: GOOD GRIEF, CHARLIE BROWN! brings together Charles M. Schulz original Peanuts cartoons.
